Section 112.4: Deadlocks (hold resource and wait)

A deadlock is what occurs when two or more threads are waiting for each other to complete or to release a

resource in such a way that they wait forever.

If thread1 holds a lock on resource A and is waiting for resource B to be released while thread2 holds resource B

and is waiting for resource A to be released, they are deadlocked.

Clicking button1 for the following example code will cause your application to get into aforementioned deadlocked

state and hang

