Section 112.8: Deadlocks (two threads waiting on each other)

A deadlock is what occurs when two or more threads are waiting for each other to complete or to release a

resource in such a way that they wait forever.

A typical scenario of two threads waiting on each other to complete is when a Windows Forms GUI thread waits for

a worker thread and the worker thread attempts to invoke an object managed by the GUI thread. Observe that with

this code example, clicking button1 will cause the program to hang.

