Section 114.2: Concurrent calls

It is possible to await multiple calls concurrently by ﬁrst invoking the awaitable tasks and then awaiting them.

public async Task RunConcurrentTasks()
{
    var firstTask = DoSomethingAsync();
    var secondTask = DoSomethingElseAsync();

    await firstTask;
    await secondTask;
}

Alternatively, Task.WhenAll can be used to group multiple tasks into a single Task, which completes when all of its

passed tasks are complete.

public async Task RunConcurrentTasks()
{
    var firstTask = DoSomethingAsync();
    var secondTask = DoSomethingElseAsync();

    await Task.WhenAll(firstTask, secondTask);
}

You can also do this inside a loop, for example:

